'''Betty Taylor''' (October 7, 1919 – June 4, 2011) was an American actress and performer, best known as "Slue Foot Sue" in [[Disneyland]]'s ''[[Golden Horseshoe Saloon|Golden Horseshoe Revue]]'', opposite [[Wally Boag]].

Taylor died on June 4, 2011, at the age of 91, the day after Wally Boag died.<ref>[http://ocresort.ocregister.com/2011/06/04/betty-taylor-played-slue-foot-sue/79437/ Disney legend Betty Taylor dies at 91] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712143737/http://ocresort.ocregister.com/2011/06/04/betty-taylor-played-slue-foot-sue/79437/ |date=July 12, 2011 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.heraldonline.com/2011/06/06/3126501/betty-taylor-played-sluefoot-sue.html Betty Taylor, played Sluefoot Sue in Disneyland revue for decades, dies at 91]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>  Her interment was in [[Seattle, Washington|Seattle's]] [[Evergreen Washelli Memorial Park]].

