== Theatrical credits ==
In 2003, Roth co-wrote and co-starred along with [[Darwin Ortiz]] in ''All of the People, All of the Time''. It also co-starred actress Ruth Williamson and was co-written by Patrick Cook. It opened in Charlotte, North Carolina, and later played in Waterford, Connecticut.<ref>Jones, Kenneth [http://www.playbill.com/news/article/81393-Charlotte-Rep-Has-Pump-Boys-With-Jim-Wann-and-World-Premiere-Magic-Show-in-2003-04 "Charlotte Rep Has Pump Boys With Jim Wann, and World Premiere Magic Show, in 2003-04"], ''Playbill Magazine'', August 29, 2003, accessed February 1, 2011.</ref><ref>Trenning, Lynn [http://www.artsavant.com/reviews/2003lmt1124.html "All of the People, All the Time Reviewed"], ''artsavant.com'', November 24, 2003, accessed February 1, 2011.</ref>

Roth has consulted for [[Ricky Jay]]'s production of ''On The Stem'' as well as ''Ricky Jay and His 52 Assistants'' in which he was credited in the program as Ricky's '53rd Assistant'.<ref>Nate [http://comradeconjuror.blogspot.com/2005/05/ricky-jay.html "Ricky Jay"], ''Comrade Conjuror Blog'', May 29, 2005, accessed February 1, 2011.</ref><ref>Roth, David [http://www.davidrothmagic.com/ "Homepage"], ''davidrothmagic.com'', accessed February 1, 2011.</ref>

